{{Infobox power station | name = Işalniţa Power Station | image = Ișalnițai hőerőmű 2016-07-10.JPG | image_caption = | country = Romania | location = [[Işalniţa, Dolj|Işalniţa]], [[Dolj County]] | coordinates = {{coord|44|23|15|N|23|43|5|E|region:RO_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | owner = [[Termoelectrica]] | status = O | th_fuel_primary = [[lignite]], [[natural gas]] | th_combined_cycle = | ps_units_operational = 2 | ps_electrical_capacity = 630 [[Watt#Megawatt|MW]] | commissioned = 1968 | decommissioned = }}
The '''Işalniţa Power Station''' is a large [[thermal power plant]] located in [[Işalniţa, Dolj|Işalniţa]], [[Dolj County]] having 2 generating groups of 315 MW each for a total of 630MW of installed capacity. The power station formerly had a total of eight generation groups, three of 50 [[Watt#Megawatt|MW]], one of 55 MW, two of 100 MW and two groups of 315 MW for a total of 1,035MW but six of these groups were decommissioned thus leaving only the two 315MW units.
A consortium formed by [[Alstom]], [[Sumitomo]] and [[IHI Corporation]] was commissioned to upgrade the 315 MW group to 345 MW each at a total cost of US$315 million.<ref>[http://www.9am.ro/stiri-revista-presei/2005-06-23/mec-vrea-14-milioane-de-euro-in-plus-pentru-cet-isalnita.html MEC vrea 14 milioane de euro in plus la Isalnita {{ro}}]</ref>
There are plans to add another generating group of 500 [[MWh]] at '''Işalniţa Power Station''' that will result a total power generating capacity of 1,535 [[MWh]]<ref>[http://www.gds.ro/Economie/2008-12-01/CE+Craiova+vrea+o+noua+termocentrala CE Craiova vrea o noua termocentrala]</ref> at a cost of US$750 million.
The tallest chimney of the power station is 200 metres tall.
