{{Infobox book series | image = | image_caption = | books = | author = (Series Editors:) Dumont, Henri J., Werger, Marinus J.A. | title_orig = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = | language = | genre = Academic literature | publisher = Kluwer Academic | pub_date = 1957 | english_pub_date = | media_type = Print, E books | number_of_books = 80 | list_books = | preceded by = Physiologia comparata et oecologia | followed by = }}
'''''Monographiae Biologicae''''' ({{ISSN|0077-0639}}) is a scholarly scientific literature review series, consisting of monographs published by [[Kluwer Academic Publishers]], an imprint of [[Springer Science+Business Media]]. The series subject area generally covers [[ecology]], [[zoology]], and [[biology]]. More specifically, the book series covers the [[biogeography]] of continental areas, including whole [[continent]]s; differentiated stand-alone [[ecosystem]]s such as islands, island groups, mountains or [[mountain chain]]s; aquatic or [[marine ecosystem]]s such as coastal systems, [[mangroves]], [[coral reefs]], and other related ecosystems. Fresh water environments are also included in this series such as major [[river basins]], lakes, and groups of lakes.
[[Taxonomy (biology)|Taxonomic]] studies include the main groups of animals, plants, [[fungi]] and the comparative ecology of major [[biome]]s.
The series continues ''Physiologia comparata et oecologia'', ({{ISSN|0369-8637}}).<ref name=Harvard> {{cite web | title = Library catalog | work = Harvard Libraries | publisher = Hollis Classic (library) | year = 2009 | url = http://lms01.harvard.edu/F/VCNKN9V97JQRQ16JQQISJHCPAU2GV2FG9IBU86M1LN3E44JYLC-18965?func=full-set-set&set_number=008056&set_entry=000001&format=999 | format = | doi = | accessdate =2013-06-30}}</ref>
==Abstracting and indexing== This series is indexed by the following services:<ref name=Harvard/>
* [[United States Department of Agriculture|Bibliography of agriculture]] (USDA) * [[Biological Abstracts]] * [[Chemical Abstracts Service]] * [[GeoRef]]
