'''Montanic acid''' is a [[saturated fat|saturated]] [[fatty acid]] isolated and detected mainly in [[montan wax]]. It also occurs in [[beeswax]] and [[Chinese wax]]. Montanic acid [[ethylene glycol]] [[ester]]s and [[glycerol]] esters are used as protective layer on fruit skins and coating on foods. <ref>"Documenta Geigy: Scientific tables" Konrad Diem, C. Lentner; Geigy Pharmaceuticals, sixth edition, 1965.</ref>
